items.name: Va'raz "Killi" Killision (Subverse) LoRA
items.description:
Pirate Queen Va'raz "Killi" Killision the Red, leader of the Dread fleet from the game Subverse by Studio FOW. Works best on 0.8-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger: "killisub, colored skin, yellow eyes, glowing eyes, no pupils, colored sclera" always needed "Eyepatch" for consistency.

Suggestions:

  • "kisb, leotard, thigh boots, eyepatch" for her main outfit keep the weight at 1.0 when prompting this one for more consistency.

  • She is quite flexible clothing wise and if needed lower the weight but beware things like the horns may start to disappear.

  • "Red skin" can help if those parts are being off.

  • The "eyepatch" tag can sometimes fail and the eye will appear in such cases just gen again or change CFG until it gets fixed. This is more a Stable diffusion issue and I have not found a way to 100% avoid this issue.

The main outfit works pretty well given the data. Considering she has a rather complex design I was able to get it very consistent where only minor issues may arise. In most cases just genning again will help fix whatever may have done wrong. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.description:
If you enjoyed this LoRA, please hit the like button and give it a 5-star rating. Your encouragement motivates me to keep creating LoRAs like this.

Model used: AbyssOrangeMix3

Recommended VAE: orangemix or kl-f8

Recommended LoRA weight: 0.8-1

(worst quality, low quality:1.4), 3d, greyscale, monochrome, text

On all images from preview I used DPM++ 2M SDE sampler, but you can use what you like.

All other settings the same as for AOM model:

Steps:

  • DPM++ SDE Karras: Test: 12ï½ ,illustration: 20ï½

  • DPM++ 2M Karras: Test: 20ï½ ,illustration: 28ï½

Clipskip: 1 or 2

Upscaler :

  • Detailed illust â†’ Latenet (nearest-exact)
    Denoise strength: 0.5 (0.5~0.6)

  • Simple upscale: Swin IR, ESRGAN, Remacri etcâ€¦
    Denoise strength: Can be set low. (0.35~0.6)

This LoRA was trained on images which I scraped from fancaps.net (I made tampermonkey extension which adds a download button under each image). I used wd14 tagger extension for Stable diffusion to automatically tag my images and LoRA trainer colab for training (90 images with 4 repeats, 2 batch size, 10 epochs).

I plan to do a lot of LoRAs based on the One Punch Man anime. If you are interested, you can follow me.

items.name: Anime Stills
items.description:
I made this model with the goal of creating flat 2d style anime themed stills. I think it came out pretty good! Merged from Flat-2D Animerge and Post-It-Note Mix.

How to use

- Clip skip: 2

- CFG scale: 8

- Sampler: Eular A, or DPM++ 2M SDE Karras,

- Sampling Steps : 20+, 40 recommended

- Upscaler (Hires. fix): 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G

- Hires steps: 14

- Denoising strength: 0.35

- Upscale by: 1.5+

- Default prompts (optional)

- Positive: best quality, masterpiece, flat, 2d, lineart (can create b&w), detailed eyes, detailed faces (these can help with anime's that have odd face structures, like dbz) ...

- Negative: worst quality, low quality, letterboxed, 3d, greyscale (to avoid b&w) ...

- Use aDetailer to help faces if you see issues, though this will cute-ify the faces a bit

  • Use face_yolov8n.pt

VAE Recommendations

  • Night Sky Yozora

  • 840000 ema pruned

  • Fantasy World VAE

Credits

Flat-2D Animerge by @bigbeanboiler

Post-It-Note Mix by @duskfallcrew
